\title{Diamond-graded monoidal categories}
\taxon{theory}
\import{macros}

\p{

The \define{theory of diamond-graded (generalized) monoidal categories} is the
modal double theory that combines the [theory of categories graded](thy-000K) by
the monoidal poset whose Hasse diagram is the diamond

\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#q=WzAsNCxbMSwyLCIoMCwwKSJdLFswLDEsIigxLDApIl0sWzIsMSwiKDAsMSkiXSxbMSwwLCIoMSwxKSJdLFswLDFdLFswLDJdLFsxLDNdLFsyLDNdXQ==
\begin{tikzcd}[sep=small]
	& {(1,1)} \\
	{(1,0)} && {(0,1)} \\
	& {(0,0)}
	\arrow[from=2-1, to=1-2]
	\arrow[from=2-3, to=1-2]
	\arrow[from=3-2, to=2-1]
	\arrow[from=3-2, to=2-3]
\end{tikzcd}
}

and monoidal product is the join with the analogue of the [theory of relative
monoidal promonads](thy-000H) that makes sense for the mode theory that is a
commutative square

\quiver{
% https://q.uiver.app/#q=WzAsNCxbMSwyLCJUPVRfeygwLDApfSJdLFswLDEsIlRfeygxLDApfSJdLFsxLDAsIlRfeygxLDEpfSJdLFsyLDEsIlRfeygwLDEpfSJdLFsxLDAsIiIsMCx7ImxldmVsIjoyfV0sWzMsMCwiIiwyLHsibGV2ZWwiOjJ9XSxbMiwxLCIiLDAseyJsZXZlbCI6Mn1dLFsyLDMsIiIsMix7ImxldmVsIjoyfV1d
\begin{tikzcd}[sep=small]
	& {T_{(1,1)}} \\
	{T_{(1,0)}} && {T_{(0,1)}} \\
	& {T=T_{(0,0)}}
	\arrow[Rightarrow, from=1-2, to=2-1]
	\arrow[Rightarrow, from=1-2, to=2-3]
	\arrow[Rightarrow, from=2-1, to=3-2]
	\arrow[Rightarrow, from=2-3, to=3-2]
\end{tikzcd}
}

of monads and monad morphisms.

}
